description.narrative: Positive practices focused on Nutrition, Health, Hygiene and Sanitation, COVID-19 prevention and socioeconomic impact mitigation were promoted through communitarian change. IYCF, health and hygiene practices have been promoted in 138 communities in 4 drought-most affected Provinces of Bié, Cunene, Huila and Namibe. 468,655 people have been reached by the CLTS program in 420 villages, with 131,446 people living in 170 communities without ODF. More than 15 million - 50% of the Angolan population - people were reached through this mass media campaign on responsible fatherhood and birth registration. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/08/2020
